      Why replacing wires with waves makes business sense
    </h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        More bandwidth in the same space (many light colours in one tiny path).
      </li>
      <li>Faster over distance — no slow, resistive wires.</li>
      <li>Lower power per bit — less heat, lower energy bills.</li>
      <li>Flexible after build — reprogram with light, not new masks.</li>
      <li>Cleaner signals — less interference and fewer errors.</li>
      <li>True 3D connections — no traffic jams inside the chip.</li>
